In this Letter, we show that the ground state of the Mott phase of $N$-color fermions on the triangular
lattice with one particle per site is a $SU(N)$ chiral spin liquid in a large parameter range if the system is subject to a
static artificial gauge field with flux $\pi/2$ per triangular plaquette. The starting point is the $SU(N)$ Hubbard Hamiltonian
